{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-jsx","path":"/projects/indoor-garden-timelapse/","result":{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p><img src=\"/40048dfd6e34e9f45348ab64bf2f66a2/timelapse.gif\" alt=\"Indoor Garden Timelapse\"></p>\n<p>Another lockdown project!</p>\n<p>For some reason I've been getting into gardening over the lockdown, from building an automatic irrigation system for our newly built vegetable patch to taking part (and winning) a sunflower growing competition, it's about the most interesting thing I could think of doing whilst being stuck in my house during a great spell of weather.</p>\n<p>This year, for my birthday I recieved an <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://amzn.to/31Xp40r\" title=\"indoor vegetable garden\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">indoor vegetable garden</a>, and thought it would be fun to set up a timelapse camera to monitor the plants growing!</p>\n<p>Since I'm currently also slightly addicted to Raspberry Pi's (now up to 4 in my collection!), I thought this would be a good use for one of them.</p>\n<p>So, I bought the <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://thepihut.com/products/adafruit-raspberry-pi-zero-w-camera-pack-includes-pi-zero\" title=\"Raspberry Pi Zero W camera combo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Raspberry Pi Zero W camera combo</a>, strapped it to the side of the garden and adjusted the focus of the camera with a pair of pliers to improve the focus a little bit.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/9568a/pi-cam.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/ba381/pi-cam.webp 200w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/7f61c/pi-cam.webp 400w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/d00b9/pi-cam.webp 800w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/92f8c/pi-cam.webp 1200w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/fad48/pi-cam.webp 1600w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/e51ec/pi-cam.webp 3024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/e07e9/pi-cam.jpg 200w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/066f9/pi-cam.jpg 400w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/4b190/pi-cam.jpg 800w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/e5166/pi-cam.jpg 1200w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/b17f8/pi-cam.jpg 1600w,\n/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/9568a/pi-cam.jpg 3024w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/c3b7d53fc7335265d4a35db8c0cdc7ec/4b190/pi-cam.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Pi Cam\"\n          title=\"Pi Cam\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The end result is this cute little video:</p>\n<p><div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.42857142857143%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <div class=\"embedVideo-container\"> <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/DiBl9JMlBUI?rel=0\" class=\"embedVideo-iframe\" style=\"border:0; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \" allowfullscreen></iframe> </div> </div></p>\n<p>This little video was the result of 2 months of growing and almost 200GB of images!\nI set up the camera to take a photo every 30 seconds (which in hindsight was a little bit too often, and the final video only took a frame each 16 minutes)</p>\n<h2>Scripts</h2>\n<p>I thought I would share the little script I used to pull images from the camera, sort them into good (clear, well exposed) and bad (too dark, fuzzy, etc), and then render them into a timelapse...</p>\n<p>Firstly, on the camera all you need is a little script that helps with actually taking the photos:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token shebang important\">#!/bin/bash</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function-name function\">take</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">DATE</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">date</span> +<span class=\"token string\">\"%Y-%m-%d_%H_%M_%S\"</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\n\n    raspistill -t <span class=\"token number\">100</span> -q <span class=\"token number\">20</span> -o /home/pi/timelapse-images/<span class=\"token variable\">$DATE</span>.jpg\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\ntake\n\n<span class=\"token function\">sleep</span> <span class=\"token number\">29</span>\n\ntake</code></pre></div>\n<p>Just <code class=\"language-text\">chmod +x</code> it and add it to the cron jobs with <code class=\"language-text\">crontab -e</code> and if you want it to run every minute, then append this to the crontab:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">* * * * * <span class=\"token function\">bash</span> /home/pi/camera.sh</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now, on another computer (preferably faster and on the same network as your RPI), you can set up a little script like:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token shebang important\">#!/bin/bash</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"!!! Requires EXTERNAL-SSD to be plugged in at all times !!!\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Retrieving latest images\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">rsync</span> -a -v --ignore-existing --remove-source-files pi@pi-cam.local:/home/pi/timelapse-images/ /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/timelapse-images\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Filtering and linking based on shutter speed to get rid of flickers - VERY SLOW STEP\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Checking and skipping a few thousand photos...\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token for-or-select variable\">f</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span> /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/timelapse-images/*.jpg\n<span class=\"token keyword\">do</span>\n    <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">fname</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">basename</span> $f<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># If not bad and not good (ie: not sorted yet), process and filter</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token operator\">!</span> -f /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/filtered-timelapse-images/<span class=\"token variable\">$fname</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token operator\">!</span> -f /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/bad-timelapse-images/<span class=\"token variable\">$fname</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">then</span>\n        <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">ss</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>exiftool -exif:shutterspeedvalue -s -s -s $f <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">cut</span> -c <span class=\"token number\">3</span>-<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\n        <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">sss</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">${ss<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>.*}</span>\n\n        <span class=\"token comment\"># If the correct shutter speed, then place in the filtered folder, else cache in the bad folder</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$sss</span>\"</span> -gt <span class=\"token number\">30</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">then</span>\n            <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> Linking <span class=\"token variable\">$fname</span>\n            <span class=\"token function\">ln</span> -s <span class=\"token variable\">$f</span> /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/filtered-timelapse-images/<span class=\"token variable\">$fname</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span>\n            <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> Caching bad photo <span class=\"token variable\">$fname</span>\n            <span class=\"token function\">ln</span> -s <span class=\"token variable\">$f</span> /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/bad-timelapse-images/<span class=\"token variable\">$fname</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">fi</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">#else</span>\n        <span class=\"token comment\">#echo Skipping $fname</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">fi</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">done</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Generating timelapse\"</span>\n\nffmpeg -r <span class=\"token number\">1920</span> -pattern_type glob -i <span class=\"token string\">'/Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/filtered-timelapse-images/*.jpg'</span> -vf <span class=\"token string\">\"transpose=1\"</span> -vcodec libx265 -r <span class=\"token number\">60</span> /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/filtered-timelapse.mp4 -y\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Done!\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">open</span> /Volumes/EXTERNAL-SSD/</code></pre></div>\n<p>This script obviously requires an external ssd, and will require some modifications for you to use.\nIt also requires <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://ffmpeg.org/\" title=\"ffmpeg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">ffmpeg</a> to be installed locally, so make sure that's all set up before any annoying errors hit you in the face.</p>\n<p>Basically all this script does is download the latest images from the RPI, delete them from the RPI once done, then filter them into symlinked directories of \"good\" and \"bad\" photos - essentially caching them.</p>\n<p>Then it triggers a rendering job that takes <em>absolutely FOREVER</em> to create a h.265 encoded timelapse of it all.\n(Originally I used h.264 but h.265 took up honestly 1/8th of the space without losing much quality which is fantastic!)</p>\n<p>P.S. The gif at the start of the page is generated with a one liner:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">ffmpeg -ss <span class=\"token number\">3</span> -t <span class=\"token number\">20</span> -i /Volumes/JARVIS-SSD/filtered-timelapse.mp4 -filter_complex <span class=\"token string\">\"[0:v] fps=10,scale=480:-1,split [a][b];[a] palettegen [p];[b][p] paletteuse\"</span> /Volumes/JARVIS-SSD/timelapse.gif</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, gifs are rather inefficient, the better option would be an <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://developers.google.com/speed/webp/faq\" title=\"animated webp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">animated webp</a> image, which is unfortunately not supported by GatsbyJS, nor some <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://caniuse.com/#search=webp\" title=\"old browsers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">old browsers</a>, but it would be 10% the size of the gif version (and better quality!) - to generate it I used the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">ffmpeg -ss <span class=\"token number\">3</span> -t <span class=\"token number\">20</span> -i /Volumes/JARVIS-SSD/filtered-timelapse.mp4 -filter_complex <span class=\"token string\">\"[0:v] fps=10,scale=640:-1\"</span> -vcodec libwebp -lossless <span class=\"token number\">1</span> -q <span class=\"token number\">30</span> -preset default -loop <span class=\"token number\">0</span> -an -vsync <span class=\"token number\">0</span> /Volumes/JARVIS-SSD/timelapse.webp -y</code></pre></div>\n<p>Hope you've enjoyed!</p>\n<p>Before:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/fa4b3/garden-patch.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/ba381/garden-patch.webp 200w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/7f61c/garden-patch.webp 400w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/d00b9/garden-patch.webp 800w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/92f8c/garden-patch.webp 1200w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/fad48/garden-patch.webp 1600w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/8fd99/garden-patch.webp 3890w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/e07e9/garden-patch.jpg 200w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/066f9/garden-patch.jpg 400w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/4b190/garden-patch.jpg 800w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/e5166/garden-patch.jpg 1200w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/b17f8/garden-patch.jpg 1600w,\n/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/fa4b3/garden-patch.jpg 3890w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/d6ef71dfe5fe22e3b5b26d3326bb270e/4b190/garden-patch.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Garden Before\"\n          title=\"Garden Before\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/d2602/garden-patch-grown.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/ba381/garden-patch-grown.webp 200w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/7f61c/garden-patch-grown.webp 400w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/d00b9/garden-patch-grown.webp 800w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/92f8c/garden-patch-grown.webp 1200w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/fad48/garden-patch-grown.webp 1600w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/b33a3/garden-patch-grown.webp 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/e07e9/garden-patch-grown.jpg 200w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/066f9/garden-patch-grown.jpg 400w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/4b190/garden-patch-grown.jpg 800w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/e5166/garden-patch-grown.jpg 1200w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/b17f8/garden-patch-grown.jpg 1600w,\n/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/d2602/garden-patch-grown.jpg 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/2ca6c6f7ef55f5edc6a56c24a76833fc/4b190/garden-patch-grown.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Garden After\"\n          title=\"Garden After\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","excerpt":"Indoor Garden Timelapse Another lockdown project! For some reason I've been getting into gardening over the lockdown, from building an automatic irrigation system for our newly built vegetable patch…","frontmatter":{"title":"📸 Indoor Garden Timelapse","date":"2020-06","tech":["Raspberry Pi","Bash"],"link":"https://youtu.be/DiBl9JMlBUI","source":null,"previewImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":1200,"height":1597,"src":"/static/b2f05c36fee688b288eeecde9e6f0ae6/47498/garden-screenshot.jpg","srcSet":"/static/b2f05c36fee688b288eeecde9e6f0ae6/47498/garden-screenshot.jpg 1x,\n/static/b2f05c36fee688b288eeecde9e6f0ae6/52258/garden-screenshot.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/b2f05c36fee688b288eeecde9e6f0ae6/50587/garden-screenshot.jpg 2x"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/indoor-garden-timelapse/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/projects/ipfs-web-hosting/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"📦 IPFS Web Hosting"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/projects/eink-dashboard/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"☔️ E-Ink Weather Dashboard"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["602281340","682078843"]}